<dl id="n33170g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33170g">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33170g"> 170(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Stealer of &mdash; <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n33170g"><li>FW 570.35 </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/lexs.htm#n33170g">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/l39s.htm#n33170g">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n33170g">MS missing</ms> </li><li>JJA not reproduced <a name="sd5" href="../../FF/fdra/sda.htm#sd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/s/sd5.htm#n33170g">Draft: III&sect;4.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The necessity of preserving the material heart was very great, and four Chapters of the Book of the Dead (XXVII.-XXXb.) were composed to prevent the heart of a man from being carried off or driven away from him in the underworld by the &ldquo;<mark>stealers of hearts</mark>&rdquo;. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1909) lxi</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n33191b" href="n33all.htm#n33191b">N33 (VI.B.4):191(b)</a></mm> </dd></dl>
